I have never really been a fan of the columns when 100% width. Let's say I have a column with just a button, when the device width is reduced to < 768px all columns are on top of each other.

I am not sure this is the best approach, but this worked for me:

```
@make-grid-columns($i: 1, $list: ".col-xs-#{$i}, .col-sm-#{$i}, .col-md-#{$i}, .col-lg-#{$i}") {
  @for $i from (1 + 1) through $grid-columns {
    $list: "#{$list}, .col-xs-#{$i}, .col-sm-#{$i}, .col-md-#{$i}, .col-lg-#{$i}";
  }
  #{$list} {
    position: relative;
    // Prevent columns from collapsing when empty
    min-height: 1px;
    // Inner gutter via padding
    padding-left:  ($grid-gutter-width / 2);
    padding-right: ($grid-gutter-width / 2);
  }

  // Added to space out the columns when they are full row width
  @media (max-width: $screen-sm-min) {
    #{$list} {
      margin-top: 10px;
      &:first-child {
        margin-top: 0;
      }
    }
  }
}
```

