The call currently is like [this](https://github.com/jquery/jquery-migrate/blob/1cb2093f4abd5cef29de645875dd397b7521798c/src/intro.js#L5):

    define( [ "jquery" ], window, factory );

AMD does not define semantics for the call pattern above. RequireJS happens to ignore the 3rd argument and treats it as `define(["jquery"], window)`. Thus it defines the module to have for value `window`. This makes loading the plugin through RequireJS ---  and most likely any AMD loader --- a complete non-starter. I've not checked what SystemJS would do with it, but it is unlikely that it would interpret it as it is meant to be interpreted. I'm wondering whether the problems reported in #272 and #273 are caused by this incorrect `define` call. Since a `define` call with the pattern above has no defined semantics, tools that aim to process AMD `define` may just crash.

It should be something like the following:

    define( [ "jquery" ], function ($) {
        return factory($, window);
    });

When I make the replacement manually in my local installation of `jquery-migrate`, it becomes usable.

